class Solution {
public:
int paintWalls(vector<int>& cost, vector<int>& time) {
    int n = cost.size();
    vector<int> f(n * 2 + 1, INT_MAX / 2);
    f[n] = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
        vector<int> g(n * 2 + 1, INT_MAX / 2);
        for (int j = 0; j <= n * 2; ++j) {
            // 付费
            if (j > 0) {
                g[j - 1] = min(g[j - 1], f[j]);
            }
            // 免费
            if (time[i] <= j) {
                g[j] = min(g[j], f[j - time[i]] + cost[i]);
            }
        }
        f = move(g);
    }
    return *min_element(f.begin() + n, f.end());
}
};

Input Specification:
Each input file contains one test case. For each case, the first line contains two positive integers n and m (1<n,m<10^5), the number of rows and columns of the matrix, and the number of operations. Then m lines follow, each describes a query in the format: typei indexi vali. Here 0 <= typei <= 1, 0 <= indexi < n, and 0 <= vali < 10^9. It is guaranteed that no two operations are performed on the same row/column.

Output Specification:
For each test case, simply output the sum of integers in the matrix after all queries are applied. Since the sum may be very large, you only have to output the sum moded by 10^9+7.

Sample Input:
3 4
0 0 1 1 0 0 10 1 2 3
1 0 1 2 0 1 100
1 1 0 0 1 2 100
0 1 2 0 1 0 1000
Sample Output:
1099

